What you need to know:

Dari, which is 13.2 kilometres from the city centre, and in the middle of an indigenous forest, was to undergo a complete makeover.To secure the loan, Dari Ltd placed the restaurant and its developments as collateral.In 2015, and after negotiating the deal, the bank asked Dari Ltd to put up $1 million (Sh100 million) towards the purchase of the land.The Sh100 million, Mr Tuju would later tell the court, was not part of the proposal.